Building Opticks on Windows
---------------------------
Opticks builds in Microsoft Visual Studio 2005 SP1 only.
 1) Set OPTICKSDEPENDENCIES to point to the dependecies directory.
 2) Rename the Opticks.vcproj.FILLINUSERNAME.user.template to Opticks.vcproj.username.user with your
    login name.
 3) Open the Opticks.sln in the "application" directory.
 4) Build the Solution.
 5) Set "Opticks" as the default project.
 6) Run Opticks.

Building Opticks on Solaris
---------------------------
Opticks requires Solaris 10 with Sun Studio 11 and scons version 0.96 or later.
scons -h will list options.
 1) Set OPTICKSDEPENDENCIES to point to the dependencies dirtory.
 2) Set LD_LIBRARY_PATH_64 to point to JDK 1.4 or later directories.
 3) cd into the "application" directory.
 4) run scons
 5) cd into the "application/PlugIns/src" directory.
 6) run scons
 7) set the OPTICKS_HOME environment variable to the "Release" directory.
 8) run solOpticks
 9) Set your plug-in path to point to "Build/Binaries-solaris-sparc-*/PlugIns" directory.
 10) Restart Opticks.
